<h2 id="module-installation">Automated Setup with install_comserv.pl</h2>
<h3>Running the Installation Script</h3>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Download the installation script:</strong>
        <pre><code>curl -O https://raw.githubusercontent.com/comserv2/Comserv/main/install_comserv.pl</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Make the script executable:</strong>
        <pre><code>chmod +x install_comserv.pl</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Run the script:</strong>
        <pre><code>./install_comserv.pl</code></pre>
        Follow the prompts to input your database connection details when prompted.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Verify the setup was successful:</strong>
        <pre><code>perl -MModule::Name -e 'print $Module::Name::VERSION'</code></pre>
        Replace <code>Module::Name</code> with the module you wish to verify.
    </li>

<h3>Installing Perl on Windows</h3>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Ensure Strawberry Perl is installed:</strong>
        Download and install from:
        <pre><code>https://strawberryperl.com/</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Run the `install_comserv.pl` script:</strong>
        Open Command Prompt and execute:
        <pre><code>perl install_comserv.pl</code></pre>
        Follow the prompts to input appropriate database connection details.
    </li>
</ol>
    </ol>
<h3>Installing Module Dependencies</h3>
    <li><strong>Use the correct Perl version:</strong>
        The `install_comserv.pl` script automatically configures the proper Perl version for you.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Ensure PATH includes Perlbrew's bin:</strong>
        Ensure `~/perl5/perlbrew/bin` and
`~/perl5/perlbrew/perls/perl-5.40.0/bin` are included.
`/home/comserv/perl5/perlbrew/perls/perl-5.40.0/bin` are included.
    </li>

    <li><strong>Set up user-level modules:</strong>
        Local module management is handled automatically by the `install_comserv.pl` script.
        Ensure you follow the input prompts during setup for best results.
    </li>

    <li><strong>Check Perl library paths:</strong>
        <pre><code>perl -e 'print join "\n", @INC'</code></pre>
        Verify paths like
`/home/comserv/perl5/perlbrew/perls/perl-5.40.0/lib/site_perl/5.40.0` are
listed.
    </li>

    <li><strong>Install Dependencies:</strong>
        The `install_comserv.pl` script automatically handles all required dependency installations.
    </li>
    <li>Create a directory for Comserv:
        <pre><code>mkdir /path/to/Comserv</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>Clone the repository into the created directory:
        <pre><code>git clone git@github.com:comserv2/Comserv.git
/path/to/Comserv</code></pre>
    <li>Navigate to the cloned directory:
        <pre><code>cd /path/to/Comserv</code></pre>
    <li>Install required modules using cpanfile:
        <pre><code>cpanm --installdeps .</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>Verify installations (e.g., of Module::Name):
        <pre><code>perl -MModule::Name -e 'print
$Module::Name::VERSION'</code></pre>
    </li>
</ol>
